<div class="flex gap-8">
  <%= render "docs/sidebar", current_page: "deployment" %>

  <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">🚀 Deployment</h1>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500">How ZTLP components are deployed to machines via SSH.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">How SSH Provisioning Works</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">
        Bootstrap deploys ZTLP components by <strong class="text-gray-900">SSH-ing into target machines</strong>
        and writing configuration files, install scripts, and systemd service definitions.
      </p>
      <div class="rounded-md bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 p-4 mt-3">
        <pre class="text-xs font-mono text-ztlp-700">Bootstrap Server
  │
  │ SSH (Net::SSH)
  ▼
Target Machine
  ├─ [1] Create /etc/ztlp/ directory
  ├─ [2] Write ztlp.toml configuration
  ├─ [3] Write & run install script
  │   ├─ Download ZTLP binary
  │   ├─ Create systemd service file
  │   └─ Reload systemd daemon
  ├─ [4] Enable ztlp service
  └─ [5] Start ztlp service</pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Deployment Methods</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <% [
          ["🎯", "Single Machine", "Machine detail → Provision. Deploys all assigned roles."],
          ["🔄", "Network Deploy", "Network page → Deploy. Provisions all pending machines at once."],
          ["🧙", "Setup Wizard", "Guided setup: create network → add machines → review → deploy all."],
          ["🔌", "Test Connection", "Verify SSH access before deploying. Runs hostname on remote."]
        ].each do |icon, title, desc| %>
          <div class="rounded-md bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 p-4">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ztlp-600 mb-1"><%= icon %> <%= title %></h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500"><%= desc %></p>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">SSH Authentication</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Bootstrap supports three SSH auth methods:</p>
      <div class="space-y-2 text-xs text-gray-500">
        <p><strong class="text-gray-700">Key:</strong> Paste a PEM private key in the machine's SSH Private Key field. Most secure.</p>
        <p><strong class="text-gray-700">Password:</strong> SSH password stored encrypted in the database.</p>
        <p><strong class="text-gray-700">Agent:</strong> Use the local SSH agent for key management.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-3 rounded-md bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 p-3">
        <p class="text-xs text-amber-700">💡 Both private keys and passwords are encrypted at rest using Rails' built-in ActiveRecord encryption.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">File Locations on Target</h2>
      <div class="rounded-md bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 p-4">
        <pre class="text-xs font-mono text-ztlp-700">/etc/ztlp/
  └── ztlp.toml          # Main configuration

/usr/local/bin/
  └── ztlp-{role}        # ZTLP binary (one per role)

/var/log/ztlp/
  └── {role}.log         # Service logs

/etc/systemd/system/
  └── ztlp-{role}.service  # systemd unit file</pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Deployment History & Audit</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">
        Every deployment is logged with full detail:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-xs text-gray-500 space-y-1 ml-4 list-disc">
        <li><strong class="text-gray-700">Status:</strong> pending → running → success/failed</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gray-700">Log output:</strong> Full SSH session captured</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gray-700">Timestamps:</strong> Start, end, and duration</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gray-700">Audit trail:</strong> All actions logged to Audit Log (viewable in UI)</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3">
        View on machine detail page, the Deployments page, or the Audit Log.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Troubleshooting</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <% [
          ["Connection Refused", "border-red-300", [
            "Verify IP address is correct and reachable",
            "Check SSH is running: ssh -p <port> <user>@<ip>",
            "Check firewall allows inbound SSH"
          ]],
          ["Authentication Failed", "border-red-300", [
            "Verify SSH user exists on target",
            "If using key auth, paste the full PEM private key",
            "Ensure PubkeyAuthentication yes in sshd_config"
          ]],
          ["Binary Download Fails", "border-amber-300", [
            "Install script uses stub URL (releases.ztlp.io)",
            "Host your own binaries and update ZTLP_BINARY_URL",
            "Pre-install binaries on machines before deploying"
          ]],
          ["Service Won't Start", "border-amber-300", [
            "Check logs: journalctl -u ztlp-{role} -f",
            "Verify config: cat /etc/ztlp/ztlp.toml",
            "Check binary: which ztlp-{role}",
            "Check permissions: ls -la /etc/ztlp/ztlp.toml"
          ]]
        ].each do |title, border, items| %>
          <div class="rounded-md bg-gray-50 border-l-4 <%= border %> p-4">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1"><%= title %></h3>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-500 space-y-1">
              <% items.each do |item| %>
                <li>• <%= item %></li>
              <% end %>
            </ul>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%= render "docs/prev_next", current_page: "deployment" %>
  </div>
</div>
